{
  "texts": [
    "This model demonstrates a persistent efficiency in error minimization offering dependable predictions that do not stray much from the observed values.",
    "The close approximation to the actual data and the ability to deal with both types of errors, absolute and relative, indicate that this is a model that can be easily applied in the realworld context of enrolment forecasting.",
    "Moreover, the greater variability insensitivity of the model also makes it reliable to facilitate the strategic planning of enrolment and retention, thus making it an essential asset for organizations that seek to utilize data in making decisions rather than guessing.",
    "This model's overall ability to detect enrolment trends accurately marks a significant improvement in both predictive stability and accuracy.",
